Day 33 – Docker Secrets & Environment Variables (Swarm)

- Initialize single-node Swarm: docker swarm init --advertise-addr <IP>
- Create secret: echo "secret" | docker secret create name -
- Use secrets in compose under 'secrets' block
- Access inside container: /run/secrets/<name>
- Environment variables via .env file and ${VAR_NAME} in compose
- Deploy stack: docker stack deploy -c docker-compose.yml <stack_name>
- Clean up: docker stack rm <stack_name>, docker secret rm <name>
- Secrets are encrypted at rest and safer than plain env vars
